### 🔴 Critical Findings

#### 1. Underscore(): Triple Regex Replace chain + `.ToLower()` — 4+ allocations per call

**Impact:** Each call allocates 3 intermediate strings (from nested `Regex.Replace`) plus a 4th from `.ToLower()`. At millions of calls, this is the dominant GC pressure source. Also affects `Kebaberize()` (L147) which chains through `Underscore()`.
**Files:** `CaseTransformExtensions.cs:L115-121`, `L147-149`
